Definition:
	A function is a group of code that should do only one task.

Syntax:
	function definition:
		Data_type function_name( arguments ) {
			return value;
		}

	function declaration:
		Data_type function_name( arguments );

Examples:
	int get_number( int arg1, char arg2 );

	...

	int get_number( int arg1, char arg2 ) {

	}
